    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Add missing nr_rrc_prepare_msg3_payload function for MSG3 handling\n\n### Summary\nThe function `nr_rrc_prepare_msg3_payload` was referenced in documentation and expected by users but was missing from the RRC NR UE implementation. This caused compilation errors when trying to prepare MSG3 payloads for initial access procedures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR_UE/rrc_proto.h`: Added function declaration for `nr_rrc_prepare_msg3_payload`\n- `openair2/RRC/NR_UE/rrc_UE.c`: Implemented the missing function as a wrapper that calls the existing `nr_rrc_ue_prepare_RRCSetupRequest` function\n\n### Reproduction\nUsers attempting to call `nr_rrc_prepare_msg3_payload` during UE initialization or random access procedures would encounter undefined reference errors during linking. The function is now available for use by the MAC layer when preparing MSG3 transmission buffers.\n\nThe implementation follows the existing pattern where RRCSetupRequest messages are generated and placed in the SRB0 RLC buffer for retrieval during MSG3 construction.\n"
}